---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Dacor Appliance Repair Los Angeles | Same Day Service";
const description = "Expert Dacor appliance repair in Los Angeles. Certified technicians for ranges, ovens, refrigerators, WineStation & all Dacor series. Same-day service, genuine OEM parts, 90-day warranty. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Dacor Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-dacor-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "Dacor Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Dacor Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Dacor Wall Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Dacor Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Dacor WineStation Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Dacor Cooktop Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Dacor Warming Drawer Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Dacor appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Dacor repairs run $175–$620. Common fixes like an igniter replacement, door gasket, or temperature sensor are on the lower end. Control board or sealed-system work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Dacor Discovery WineStation units?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. We repair the Dacor Discovery WineStation — the preservation system designed to keep open bottles fresh for up to 60 days. Common issues: compressor failure, temperature control fault, seal system problems, and dispensing mechanism failure. Parts availability is good through Dacor/Samsung supply channels."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Dacor now owned by Samsung?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016. Current Dacor Modernist Collection appliances incorporate Samsung electronics and platform technology. This actually improves parts availability and diagnostic capability for newer models. Legacy Dacor (Discovery, Renaissance, Distinctive series) uses pre-acquisition Dacor-specific components — we carry parts for both generations."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service all Dacor series — Discovery, Renaissance, Distinctive, and Modernist?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — all Dacor series across all generations. Discovery and Renaissance (pre-2016), Distinctive and Classic, and the current Modernist Collection. Legacy models use Dacor-specific components; Modernist Collection incorporates Samsung platform technology. We carry parts for both and diagnose accordingly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are the most common Dacor failures in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Igniter failure on SimmerSear burners (coastal salt air accelerates ceramic corrosion), Pure Convection fan issues causing uneven oven temperature, control board faults on older Discovery and Renaissance series, and WineStation compressor problems. We see all of these regularly across LA."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair older legacy Dacor models from the Discovery and Renaissance era?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Legacy Dacor Discovery and Renaissance appliances are well worth repairing — they were built to high quality standards and parts are available through Dacor's supply network. We service all model years and carry common legacy Dacor components on the truck."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-blue { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-blue .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }
  .tip-wine { border-color: #7a2a5a; background: #fff0f8; }
  .tip-wine .tip-label { color: #7a2a5a; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  /* Generation timeline */
  .gen-timeline { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .gen-card { background: #161616; padding: 20px; }
  .gen-era { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .gen-name { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .gen-desc { font-size: 13px; color: #888; line-height: 1.5; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-la { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-legacy { background: #555; }
  .tag-wine { background: #7a2a5a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Dacor Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Dacor Repair.<br/>
        <span>Legacy &amp; Modern.</span><br/>
        All Series.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From the Discovery WineStation to the current Modernist Collection — we service every Dacor generation. Five decades of American-made appliances, now backed by Samsung engineering. We know both eras, carry parts for both, and repair the WineStation that most shops have never seen.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Dacor Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">All Dacor Series — Legacy &amp; Modernist</span>
    <span class="trust-item">WineStation Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Genuine Dacor OEM Parts</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 01 — ABOUT DACOR -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Dacor</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">50 Years from Monrovia, CA — Now with Samsung Behind It</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Dacor started in 1965 in Monrovia, California — a family business that grew into one of the premier American luxury appliance brands by pioneering technologies that are now industry standards: the self-cleaning built-in wall oven, the first professional range with sealed burners, Pure Convection technology. For decades, Dacor was genuinely made in the USA by the same family, and that heritage is still alive in thousands of Discovery, Renaissance, and Distinctive series appliances across Southern California.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      In 2016, Samsung acquired Dacor. The current Modernist Collection incorporates Samsung platform technology — better electronics, improved connectivity features, and access to Samsung's supply chain for parts. This is practically good news for repair: modern Dacor appliances are easier to source parts for than many pure-luxury European brands. We service both generations fluently, with different diagnostic approaches for each.
    </p>

    <div class="gen-timeline">
      <div class="gen-card">
        <div class="gen-era">Pre-2016 · Legacy</div>
        <div class="gen-name">Discovery &amp; Renaissance</div>
        <div class="gen-desc">American-made, Dacor-specific components. SimmerSear burner, Pure Convection, Discovery WineStation. Parts available through Dacor supply network.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-card">
        <div class="gen-era">Pre-2016 · Value</div>
        <div class="gen-name">Distinctive &amp; Classic</div>
        <div class="gen-desc">Mid-tier Dacor with signature features — continuous grates, GlideRacks, sealed burners. Strong build quality, parts well-documented.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-card">
        <div class="gen-era">Post-2016 · Current</div>
        <div class="gen-name">Modernist Collection</div>
        <div class="gen-desc">Samsung-backed engineering. Improved electronics, smart connectivity, contemporary design. Samsung platform familiarity helps diagnostics and parts sourcing.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-blue" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🔧 Samsung Acquisition — What It Means for Repair</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Since Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016, the Modernist Collection uses Samsung electronics and platform architecture. Our extensive experience with Samsung appliances — we repair hundreds across LA — directly applies to modern Dacor diagnostics. Control board families, sensor types, and error code structures share lineage. For legacy Discovery and Renaissance models, we rely on Dacor-specific components through the established supply network. Both paths lead to the same result: same-day repair with OEM parts.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 — SERVICES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Dacor Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All series, all generations. Same-day availability across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Range &amp; Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gas, dual-fuel, and induction ranges across all Dacor series. The SimmerSear burner on Discovery and Renaissance models has a dual-ring design similar to Thermador — it requires model-specific OEM igniters. Modernist Collection induction ranges use Samsung-platform electronics for diagnostics.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: SimmerSear igniter failure · burner won't light · oven temperature off · induction zone dead · continuous grate damage · control board · door gasket · dual-fuel ignition</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Dacor single, double, and combination wall ovens. Pure Convection — Dacor's third-element convection system that circulates heated air rather than fan-blowing existing oven heat — produces even baking results when working correctly. When it fails, one side of the oven runs hot. We diagnose the convection element and fan separately.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: Pure Convection element failure · uneven baking · temperature fluctuation · door hinge · self-clean lock · heating element · temperature sensor · control board</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍷</div>
        <div class="service-name">Discovery WineStation Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Dacor's unique wine preservation system — designed to maintain up to four open bottles for up to 60 days using an argon gas displacement system combined with precise temperature control. This is a specialty repair that most general appliance companies decline entirely. We service the compressor, temperature control circuit, dispensing mechanism, and seal system.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · temperature drift · dispensing mechanism failure · compressor · temperature sensor · seal system · argon system · control board · door gasket</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Dacor Discovery 48" and 42" built-in refrigerators, integrated panel-ready models, and column units. The Ingredient Care Center drawer — an electronically-controlled temperature-adjustable compartment for specialty items — is a frequent service point. PrecisePour water dispensing systems also require specific diagnosis when flow stops.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · Ingredient Care Center temperature fault · PrecisePour dispenser · ice maker · door gasket · compressor · control board · condenser coil service</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔆</div>
        <div class="service-name">Warming Drawer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">All Dacor warming drawer models. Dacor warming drawers are frequently paired with their wall ovens in custom kitchen designs — when both fail simultaneously (which sometimes happens after a power surge), we diagnose whether the issue is shared electronics or separate component failures.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not heating · overheating · temperature calibration · drawer mechanism · thermostat · heating element · control board · drawer alignment</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">💨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Ventilation &amp; Microwave Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Dacor wall hoods, island hoods with variable infinite speed fans, and built-in microwave ovens. Dacor's ventilation hoods use a different motor design than most — the variable-speed blower requires model-specific replacement when the speed selector fails. We also service the combination microwave-convection ovens in the Discovery and Modernist lines.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: hood motor failure · speed selector fault · microwave not heating · lighting · magnetron · control panel · duct restriction</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-wine" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🍷 Discovery WineStation — The Repair Nobody Else Does</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Dacor's Discovery WineStation is one of the most distinctive appliances the brand ever made — a preservation system that uses argon gas displacement to keep open bottles fresh for up to 60 days while maintaining precise serving temperature. Most appliance companies have never serviced one. We have. Common failure: the compressor loses efficiency over time, causing temperature drift that shortens preservation time. Secondary: the dispensing mechanism develops stiction or leaks at the pour spout seal. We carry compressor and dispensing components for the WineStation through Dacor's supply network.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 — TECHNOLOGY -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Dacor Technology — And What Breaks</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Understanding what makes Dacor appliances distinctive explains how they fail — and why generic diagnosis misses the actual cause.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Pure Convection (Third Element)</strong> — Dacor's convection system uses a dedicated heating element surrounding the convection fan, rather than pushing air from an existing element. When it fails, the oven temperature becomes uneven side-to-side and top-to-bottom. We test the Pure Convection element resistance and the fan motor speed independently before recommending parts.</li>
        <li><strong>SimmerSear Burner</strong> — Discovery and Renaissance gas ranges feature the SimmerSear burner with a high-heat outer ring and precision inner sear ring. Like Thermador's dual-stack, the ceramic igniter is geometry-specific — generic igniters don't align with the dual-ring configuration. We carry OEM Dacor SimmerSear igniters.</li>
        <li><strong>Continuous Platform Grates</strong> — Dacor's 14" extra-wide continuous grates span multiple burners as a single surface. When a grate cracks or chips (cast iron, heavy use), it throws the whole cooking surface geometry off. Replacement grates are available through Dacor supply; we source them with the repair.</li>
        <li><strong>GlideRacks</strong> — Dacor's ball-bearing oven rack system. The most common failure: the bearing cage cracks after years of thermal cycling, causing the rack to stick or drag. OEM GlideRack replacement restores the original smooth operation. We carry common sizes.</li>
        <li><strong>Modernist Collection Electronics</strong> — Post-2016 Dacor uses Samsung platform electronics. Error codes, control board families, and sensor types share heritage with Samsung appliances. Our Samsung diagnostic experience applies directly — faster fault isolation, better parts prediction.</li>
        <li><strong>Ingredient Care Center</strong> — The Discovery refrigerator's electronically-controlled specialty drawer maintains independent temperature for cheese, produce, and meat. When the drawer's temperature sensor fails, it runs continuously or not at all. OEM sensor replacement, same-day in most cases.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🌊 LA Climate + Dacor</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Coastal homes (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica) see accelerated SimmerSear igniter corrosion from salt air — the ceramic tips corrode within 2–3 years vs. 5–7 years inland. Santa Ana wind events drive fine dust into Dacor convection systems and condenser coils faster than standard seasonal wear. We factor climate zone into our maintenance recommendations for every Dacor service call.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#1a0a0a; border-color:var(--red); margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label">⚡ Legacy vs Modernist — Different Diagnostic Paths</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Pre-2016 Dacor uses proprietary Dacor control boards and sensors — diagnosis requires Dacor-specific fault code knowledge. Post-2016 Modernist Collection uses Samsung platform electronics — we apply Samsung diagnostic protocols. Using the wrong approach wastes time and leads to incorrect parts orders. We identify the generation before opening the unit.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Dacor Failures in Los Angeles</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Dacor failures follow predictable patterns by generation. Knowing the series tells us where to look first.</p>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 SimmerSear Burner Won't Ignite</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Ceramic igniter failure — either corrosion (coastal properties) or cracking from thermal cycling. The SimmerSear dual-ring configuration requires an OEM geometry-specific igniter. Generic igniters don't reach the inner ring correctly, causing intermittent spark even when new. We test each ring independently and replace only failed igniters.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Uneven Oven Baking (Pure Convection)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Pure Convection element failure — the dedicated third heating element surrounding the convection fan has failed or partially shorted. Result: uneven temperature distribution, with one side or the top running hotter. We test the element resistance, the fan speed, and the temperature sensor before ordering parts.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍷 WineStation Temperature Drift</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Compressor efficiency loss over time — the WineStation's compressor gradually loses capacity, resulting in temperatures that run 5–8°F warmer than set point. Early sign: bottles don't stay as cold as they used to. Left unaddressed, the temperature drift accelerates. Compressor replacement extends WineStation life by years.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-wine">WineStation</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">⚡ Control Board Fault (Discovery/Renaissance)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Pre-2016 Dacor control boards are more susceptible to failure than the Samsung-era electronics. Causes: power surge damage (LA's aging electrical infrastructure in older neighborhoods), moisture ingress from oven steam, or simple age failure on boards that are now 15+ years old. We diagnose the board vs. component failure before recommending replacement.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-legacy">Legacy Models</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">❄️ Refrigerator Ingredient Care Not Cooling</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">The Ingredient Care Center drawer uses an independent temperature sensor and damper system. When the sensor fails, the damper stays closed and the drawer runs warm — critical for the meats and cheeses it's designed to preserve. OEM sensor replacement, usually same-day. We also check the damper actuator which fails on the same interval.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔆 GlideRack Sticking or Dragging</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Ball-bearing cage failure from thermal cycling — the polymer bearing cage becomes brittle after years of oven heat cycling. The rack starts to drag or stick mid-extension. Not a safety issue, but a daily-use annoyance in a high-use kitchen. OEM GlideRack replacement restores original operation. We carry common Dacor rack sizes on the truck.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

