<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">09 — FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Dacor Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How much does Dacor appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most Dacor repairs run $175–$620. SimmerSear igniter replacement or GlideRack service is on the lower end. Pure Convection element, WineStation compressor, or control board work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you repair the Dacor Discovery WineStation?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — and this is a specialty. The WineStation requires knowledge of the argon preservation system, compressor circuit, dispensing mechanism, and temperature control. Most appliance companies have never serviced one. We have. Common failure: compressor efficiency loss causing temperature drift. We replace the compressor assembly and verify the full preservation system before leaving.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is Dacor now owned by Samsung, and does that affect repairs?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016. Current Modernist Collection appliances use Samsung platform electronics, which actually improves diagnostic capability and parts availability. Legacy Discovery, Renaissance, and Distinctive models use pre-acquisition Dacor-specific components. We diagnose and source parts differently for each generation — identifying which era the appliance is from is step one of every Dacor service call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can you repair older Dacor Discovery and Renaissance appliances?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Legacy Dacor Discovery and Renaissance appliances are well worth repairing — they were built to high quality standards and parts are available through Dacor's supply network. We service all model years. A 15-year-old Dacor Discovery range with a failed SimmerSear igniter or a GlideRack issue is a completely straightforward repair.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is Pure Convection and how does it fail?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Dacor's Pure Convection uses a dedicated heating element surrounding the convection fan — it heats air before circulating it, rather than fan-blowing existing oven heat. When it fails, baking results become uneven, typically with one side running hotter. We test the Pure Convection element resistance and the fan speed separately before ordering parts. Element replacement is the most common fix.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How often should Dacor appliances be serviced in Los Angeles?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Annually for ranges and cooktops in regular use. Dacor Discovery refrigerators should have condenser coil cleaning every 12–18 months (Pasadena, the Valley, and hillside homes faster). The WineStation benefits from annual compressor and preservation system check — catching early efficiency loss before it becomes a failure. Coastal properties: SimmerSear igniter inspection annually due to salt air corrosion.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

